{"key":"processedPost-13379659","value":{"id":13379659,"first":13379471,"last":13410414,"when":1287936985,"utime":"10/24/10 07:16 PM","content":"Is your shotgun terrarium in a closet or something?&nbsp; Your problem is from the caps being too wet for too long.&nbsp; It could be verticillium, in which case the only real cure is to discard the current grow and start over fresh.<br /><br />When you mist, the caps should be dry within fifteen minutes.&nbsp; If not, mist less or find a way to increase fresh air exchange.&nbsp; A shotgun terrarium up on blocks in an open room should result in the above.&nbsp; If not, move it to a better area or fan more.&nbsp; Don't allow the caps to remain wet for more than a few minutes after misting.<br />RR","title":"Re: Rotting caps... Can you identify this problem? *pics*"}}